article_text:
WASHINGTON—Accenture LLP, a consulting giant that was tapped in January to help fix the embattled HealthCare.gov, on Monday said it won a five year, $563 million contract to continue its work on the federal insurance site.

The work will fall to Accenture Federal Services, a subsidiary based in Arlington, Va., which in January won a one-year contract to continue technical improvements to the site after the government chose not to renew a contract with CGI Group Inc.
